 harris semiconductor most of the wireless startups in south brevard county were founded and are staffed by former harris corporation engineers and technicianscitation needed the companys digital telephone systems dts division was sold to teltronics in  harris was named one of the top hundred federal contractors by defense news in january  wired magazine ranked harris corporation—tied with us marshals service—as the number two threat to privacy and communications on the internet contents  history  business segments  communication systems  electronic systems  space and intelligence systems  cellsite simulators  list of harris acquisitions  see also  references  external links historyedit harris mrc processor the harris automatic press company was founded by alfred s harris in niles ohio in  the company spent the next  years developing lithographic processes and printing presses before acquiring typesetting company intertype corporation in  harris acquired gates radio a producer of broadcast transmitters and associated electronics gear but kept the gates brand name alive by putting the gates sticker on the back of numerous transmitters that were labeled harris on the front panels in  they acquired microwave technology company prd electronics of brooklyn new yorkcitation needed in  they merged with radiation inc of melbourne florida a developer of antenna integrated circuit and modem technology used in the space race the company headquarters was moved from cleveland to melbourne in citation needed in  harris corporation acquired rf communications and farinon furthering its microwave assets the printing operations were sold off in  and are now known as gss printing equipment gss printing equipment later acquired lanier worldwide which itself was spun off from harris corporation in the late scitation neededclarification needed in  harris formed a semiconductor joint venture matra harris semiconductors mhs from which harris withdrew in  after further changes mhs was taken over by atmel in  harris acquired ges semiconductor business which at this time also incorporated the intersil and rca semiconductor businesses these were combined with harris existing semiconductor businesses which were then spun off in  as an independent company under the intersil name in  harris corporation formed a joint venture with shenzhen telecom company to produce and sell harris digital microwave radios and integrate them with other systemscitation neededclarification needed in november  harris sold its commercial and standard military logic semiconductor product lines to texas instruments which included the hchct cd acact and fct product families harris retained production of the radiation hardened versions of these products in  the corporation spent  million on research and development harris corporation developed a hand held computer for use during the address canvassing portion of the  united states census secured access via a fingerprint swipe guaranteed that only the verified user had access to the unit a gps capacity was integral to the daily address management and the transfer of information that was gathered of major importance was the security and integrity of the personal and private information of the populace in january  harris reopened its calgary alberta avionics operation harris canada inc the expanded facilitys operations include among others the support of the work to be completed under the companys sixyear  million cad services contract with the government of canada for the cf avionics optimized weapon system support owss program on december  harris corporation sold its broadcast equipment operations to the gores group which operates as harris broadcast harris received m for the transaction exactly half of what it paid seven years earlier for leitch technology its final acquisition for the broadcast division on may   the purchase of competitor exelis inc was finalized almost doubling the size of the original company in july  harris corporation sold its healthcare division harris healthcare solutions to nanthealth in january  harris sold off its government it services division to veritas capital for  million business segmentsedit communication systemsedit the harris communication systems segment serves markets in tactical and airborne radios night vision technology and defense and public safety networks electronic systemsedit the harris electronic systems segment provides products and services in electronic warfare air traffic management avionics wireless technology ci undersea systems and aerostructures electronic systems es division provides the alq radio frequency jamming equipment for the us navys fa hornet aircraft the alq was originally developed by exelis es which harris acquired in  es is also a provider of components in the avionics package and targeting systems for the us navys fa and ea growlers space and intelligence systemsedit the harris space and intelligence systems segment provides capabilities in earth observation weather geospatial monitoring space protection and intelligence including sensors and payloads ground processing and information analytics cellsite simulatorsedit harris corporation produces multiple cellsite simulator products such as the stingray and hailstorm phone trackers see table below these masquerade as legitimate cellphone towers duping mobile devices to connect to them instead of real cellular networks so all wireless voice and data traffic originating in a given area are intercepted by the systems enabling stingray operators to conduct mass surveillance and triangulate the position of mobile devices originally developed for the us navy and later used in the global war on terror outside the us theyve increasingly been used by us police agencies more than six us federal agencies use these platforms including the fbi drug enforcement administration and immigration and customs enforcement the american civil liberties union aclu says at least  law enforcement agencies in  states use this or similar devices these platforms are controversial as they surveil communications of all mobile devices in their vicinity including those of individuals not suspected of any crimes harris have been criticized by civil rights advocates for requiring local municipalities police and state governments to enter into nondisclosure agreements nda and to conceal usage of these platforms from citizens and the courts such nda may violate public record and open access laws the aclu electronic privacy information center epic electronic frontier foundation eff filed two successful civil lawsuits over denied freedom of information act foia requests and violations of the public records laws of florida in september  as a result of successful litigation aclu received documents and emails between harris corporation and the federal communications commission relating to fcc approval of harris surveillance systems aclu then sent a letter to fcc stating in their view harris misled fcc office of engineering and technology staff during the regulatory review process by falsely claiming the systems were only used in emergency situations and not criminal investigations in  harris employees directly conducted wireless surveillance using stingray units on behalf of the palm bay police department—where harris has a campus—in response to a bomb threat against a middle school the search was conducted without a warrant or judicial oversight in  santa clara county withdrew from contract negotiations with harris for stingray units noting the reason was the onerous restrictions imposed by harris on what could be released under public records requests mobile phone monitoring products from harris corp product introduced cost features stingray   imsicatcher gathers information from mobile phones including location and metadata stingray ii   imsicatcher gathers information from mobile phones including location and metadata kingfish   surveillance transceiver for tracking mobile phones amberjack   directional antenna used to help track mobile phones used in conjunction with stingray gossamer and kingfish harpoon  – linear amplifier to boost the signal of a stingray or kingfish hailstorm   imsi catcher gathers information from mobile phones including location and metadata also can intercept content gossamer   imsi catcher smaller than stingray can be used for denialofservice attacks on phones triggerfish  – intercepts mobile conversations in real time may be obsolete list of harris acquisitionsedit farinon  tw  cb sheridan company  prd electronics  gates radio  intertype corporation  exelis inc  carefx  schlumberger global communications services gcs division  caprock communications  signacert  solacom atc solutions  tyco electronics macom wireless systems  crucial security inc  zandar technologies ltd  multimax  aastra digital video  optimal solutions inc  leitch technology  orkand corporation  – now harris it services encoda systems  imagelinks inc  hirschmann multimedia communications network  exigent international inc  wavtrace inc  lucent technologies pointtopoint microwave business  louth automation  audio broadcast group inc  pacific research  engineering corporation  choice microsystems  intraplex inc  agfa copying systems inc  transcomp inc  – spun off with lanier worldwide northeast broadcast lab  novatel communications  triplett corporations cellular and telecommunications business  see alsoedit positiveid a us government contracted floridabased biotech company that specializes in tracking tech for the us military referencesedit  httpsfinanceyahoocomquotehrsfinancialsphrs  surveillance harris corporation january   retrieved april    rf and microwave development and systems harris corporation january   retrieved april    electronic warfare harris corporation january   retrieved april    brevard county public schools  october   httpspecialdefensenewscomtop  the most dangerous people on the internet right now wiredcom wired magazine 