ust  the portable stingray device impersonates a cellphone tower electronically fooling all nearby mobile phones — not just the suspects phone — to send their signals into an lapd computer that signal reveals to police the location of phones in real time   valentinodevries jennifer  october  judge questions tools that grab cellphone data on innocent people the wall street journal retrieved  june    florida department of law enforcement harris corporation  june  fdle nondisclosure agreement with the harris corporation pdf american civil liberties union retrieved  march    mike masnick  june  new emails show that feds instructed police to lie about using stingray mobile phone snooping techdirt retrieved  august  police were claiming that nondisclosure agreements prevented them from getting a warrant to use the technology   nathan freed wessler  march  police hide use of cell phone tracker from courts because manufacturer asked american civil liberties union retrieved  august  police opted not to get warrants authorizing either their use of the stingray or the apartment search incredibly this was apparently because they had signed a nondisclosure agreement with the company that gave them the device   as secretive stingray surveillance tool becomes more pervasive questions over its illegality increase electronic frontier foundation retrieved  december    victory judge releases information about police use of stingray cell phone trackers american civil liberties union retrieved  december    doj emails show feds were less than explicit with judges on cell phone tracking tool american civil liberties union retrieved  december    nathan freed wessler nicole ozer  september  documents suggest maker of controversial surveillance tool misled the fcc american civil liberties union retrieved  september    aclu and aclu of northern california letter to fcc pdf american civil liberties union  september  p  retrieved  september    nail derrol  february  harris corporation opens new tech center in palm bay myfoxorlandocom wofl fox broadcasting company retrieved  april    farivar cyrus  february  powerful stingrays used to go after  hangup atm burglary ars technica retrieved  march  palm bay police department simply borrowed a stingray directly from its manufacturer the harris corporation—located down the road in melbourne florida—to respond to a  bomb threat at a school absent any judicial oversight   detective m j pusatere  pbpd stingray records bates stamped redacted pdf acluorg palm bay police department american civil liberties union p  retrieved  march    aaronson trevor  february  aclu releases florida stingray documents fcirorg florida center for investigative reporting retrieved  april    rivero daniel  march  its now a trend third court orders the release of phonetracking stingray documents fusionnet fusion retrieved  april    farivar cyrus  may  in rare move silicon valley county gov’t kills stingray acquisition ars technica retrieved  may  what happened was we were in negotiations with harris and we couldnt get them to agree to even the most basic criteria we have in terms of being responsive to public records requests   gallagher ryan  september  meet the machines that steal your phones data ars technica retrieved  august    harris corporation amberjack stingray stingray ii kingfish wireless surveillance products price list city of miami harris corp public intelligence  september  retrieved  august  this price list for harris corporation wireless surveillance products was published on the website of the city of miami   harris corporation putting the sting in mobile location tracking insider surveillance  july  retrieved  august    gillum jack  march  police keep quiet about celltracking technology associated press yahoo news retrieved  august  police didnt comply with the states publicrecords law because they did not fully disclose stingrayrelated records and allowed harris corp to dictate what information could be made public   ha